I don't have a dream.

00:25:26.254 --> 00:25:30.425
I'm only working here because I started
as a part-timer and never left.

00:25:31.134 --> 00:25:33.970
So you're in training.

00:25:34.721 --> 00:25:36.723
Just like me.

00:25:39.059 --> 00:25:40.477
Let's do our best.

00:25:41.478 --> 00:25:42.520
You can do it!

00:25:47.359 --> 00:25:48.443
Oh, that's it.

00:25:48.526 --> 00:25:51.571
Can you make a dish that even Koreans

00:25:51.654 --> 00:25:53.865
who don't like slimy textures would enjoy?

00:25:55.116 --> 00:25:58.078
That's a pretty tall order.

00:25:58.161 --> 00:26:01.790
Oh, you will be able to do it, Taiga.

00:26:01.873 --> 00:26:04.376
You're able to make
such delicious onigiri, after all.

00:26:07.212 --> 00:26:08.463
It'll be fine.

00:26:09.672 --> 00:26:10.632
I'm sure.

00:26:22.143 --> 00:26:24.938
Okay. I'll give it a try.

00:26:30.944 --> 00:26:32.278
Korean pancake with natto.

00:26:47.168 --> 00:26:49.170
Bibim-guksu with mekabu seaweed.

00:27:15.113 --> 00:27:17.782
Okra wrapped in samgyeopsal.

00:27:30.086 --> 00:27:31.671
Thank you for the food.

00:27:36.676 --> 00:27:38.052
I'm stuffed.

00:27:38.761 --> 00:27:41.389
Thank you for today.

00:27:42.223 --> 00:27:44.559
I have a good idea of what to do now.

00:27:45.560 --> 00:27:47.687
No, thank you.

00:27:49.355 --> 00:27:52.817
Make sure you let me know
when you've perfected the dish.

00:27:52.901 --> 00:27:53.818
Yes.

00:28:02.660 --> 00:28:07.040
In Korea, you add your own contact info
into the other person's phone.

00:28:38.780 --> 00:28:41.783
I need to take out the trash
before I leave.

00:28:45.703 --> 00:28:48.706
Okay. Bye then.

00:29:28.705 --> 00:29:32.166
Want to go to that
makgeolli place we went to last time?

00:29:32.876 --> 00:29:35.587
Sorry, I already ate.

00:29:36.629 --> 00:29:37.547
Oh really?

00:29:37.630 --> 00:29:39.841
Well, since I'm here,
I'll give you a ride home.

00:29:42.135 --> 00:29:42.969
‎Let's go.

00:30:30.183 --> 00:30:31.017
It's good.

00:30:32.477 --> 00:30:35.897
-I'm impressed, Taiga.
-Thank you.

00:30:38.066 --> 00:30:43.655
But for our customers, we might want
to bring down the spiciness a little bit.

00:30:44.948 --> 00:30:46.658
Okay, I'll try that.

00:30:51.621 --> 00:30:52.455
SECOND WOMEN'S DORM

00:30:52.538 --> 00:30:54.999
It's already been a week,

00:30:55.833 --> 00:30:58.711
and I still haven't received any word.

00:30:59.712 --> 00:31:01.631
I told you, "Don't think about it."

00:31:02.924 --> 00:31:04.467
Japanese men

00:31:04.550 --> 00:31:08.471
don't contact you
unless there is a reason to.

00:31:09.555 --> 00:31:14.102
Well then, how are you supposed to
get to know them better?

00:31:15.687 --> 00:31:19.190
You'll just have to take your time
with this one.

00:31:21.192 --> 00:31:23.653
It may take at least half a year.

00:31:24.445 --> 00:31:25.613
Half a year?

00:31:29.200 --> 00:31:30.952
Who is it? Onigiri Man?

00:31:31.995 --> 00:31:34.998
KAEDE REAL ESTATE

00:31:50.805 --> 00:31:56.936
HELLO, RIN
THANKS TO YOU, OUR NEW MENU ITEM IS SET

00:32:06.529 --> 00:32:09.907
RIN - HOW ARE YOU DOING?

00:32:22.295 --> 00:32:23.212
Taiga,

00:32:23.296 --> 00:32:25.840
sorry for contacting you out of the blue.

00:32:26.424 --> 00:32:28.718
No problem,
I was just leaving work anyway.

00:32:29.886 --> 00:32:30.887
Also…

00:32:32.138 --> 00:32:34.432
-I'm doing good.
-Huh?

00:32:35.641 --> 00:32:37.477
Oh, I'm glad.

00:32:38.144 --> 00:32:39.979
But… um…

00:32:40.646 --> 00:32:43.900
I didn't hear from you, so I was worried.

00:32:45.818 --> 00:32:46.778
I'm sorry.

00:32:47.445 --> 00:32:51.032
It was officially added to the menu today,

00:32:51.115 --> 00:32:53.826
-so I was going to contact you--
-That's not what I mean.

00:32:54.327 --> 00:32:58.164
I mean keeping in touch
about normal, ordinary stuff.

00:33:00.416 --> 00:33:02.919
Normal, ordinary stuff?

00:33:04.128 --> 00:33:07.632
Sharing things about your everyday life,

00:33:08.257 --> 00:33:10.927
like what you saw and what you ate.

00:33:12.804 --> 00:33:15.014
In order to get to know each other.

00:33:19.060 --> 00:33:19.977
But…

00:33:21.437 --> 00:33:24.941
wouldn't that make your boyfriend upset?

00:33:25.650 --> 00:33:26.692
Boyfriend?

00:33:28.277 --> 00:33:29.362
The other day,

00:33:30.279 --> 00:33:33.533
he came to pick you up from the restaurant
in his car.

00:33:35.952 --> 00:33:37.495
Jun-ho!

00:33:37.578 --> 00:33:40.665
He's just a friend.
I don't have a boyfriend!

00:33:51.008 --> 00:33:55.513
Taiga, do you have a girlfriend?

00:34:01.018 --> 00:34:02.103
No, I don't.

00:34:09.819 --> 00:34:10.778
Rain…

00:34:15.908 --> 00:34:19.036
-Let's run and find some shelter.
-Okay.

00:34:58.159 --> 00:34:59.243
It's like The Classic.

00:35:01.662 --> 00:35:02.872
The Classic.

00:35:03.581 --> 00:35:07.335
This is like a scene
out of my favorite movie.

00:35:36.447 --> 00:35:37.865
Wow!

00:36:03.683 --> 00:36:04.892
Please, use this.

00:36:24.787 --> 00:36:26.872
No, it's just… It's been a while

00:36:27.456 --> 00:36:29.125
since I used a handkerchief.

00:36:30.376 --> 00:36:31.794
Thank you.

00:36:43.222 --> 00:36:46.934
It's strange…
I was feeling down just a minute ago,

00:36:47.643 --> 00:36:51.564
but after running in the rain,
I feel much better.

00:36:54.775 --> 00:36:57.028
Something's making you feel down?

00:37:02.116 --> 00:37:04.952
Right now, I'm searching
for a new place to live, but…

00:37:06.912 --> 00:37:08.539
my application was rejected.

00:37:18.049 --> 00:37:20.885
When I messaged you, "How are you doing?"

00:37:21.635 --> 00:37:22.636
I think

00:37:24.138 --> 00:37:27.099
I was subconsciously asking myself that.

00:37:34.523 --> 00:37:36.776
But I can't give up.

00:37:37.485 --> 00:37:40.529
Because I want to stay in Japan
a little while longer.

00:37:48.996 --> 00:37:49.997
Um…

00:38:00.174 --> 00:38:02.510
Sorry, what were you saying?

00:38:05.888 --> 00:38:07.598
Can I help you search?

00:38:09.016 --> 00:38:09.892
What?

00:38:12.019 --> 00:38:13.187
If you…

00:38:14.105 --> 00:38:15.147
‎don't mind.

00:38:28.702 --> 00:38:30.830
-You are amazing, Rin.
-Amazing?

00:38:31.622 --> 00:38:33.165
What about it is amazing?

00:38:33.249 --> 00:38:34.500
PREVIEW

00:38:34.583 --> 00:38:36.127
When I'm with you,

00:38:37.378 --> 00:38:40.506
I feel like I can move forward.

